cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of drones as cellular base stations to improve network performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes algorithms to autonomously control the repositioning of the drone, which involves robotics and control systems. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The use of drones as base stations involves coordination and communication between multiple agents (drones and mobile user equipment), which falls under the scope of multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the control and optimization of the drone's movement to improve network performance, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the tradeoff between spectral efficiency and energy efficiency of the drone, which involves information theory and optimization.
